---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="How health4.ai works — connect your Apple Health data to any AI"
  description="Set up health4.ai in under 5 minutes. Download the app, ask your AI to create your data table, paste one token, and your health data is live."
>
  <nav class="flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <a href="/" class="text-green-400 font-bold text-lg tracking-tight hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity">health4.ai</a>
    <div class="flex gap-6 text-sm text-neutral-500">
      <a href="/compare" class="hover:text-neutral-300 transition-colors">Compare</a>
      <a href="/mcp-tools" class="hover:text-neutral-300 transition-colors hidden sm:inline">MCP tools</a>
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-300 transition-colors">Home</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="px-6 py-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">How health4.ai works</h1>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-12">
      Apple blocks cloud access to your health data by design — there is no server API, no webhook, no OAuth flow.
      health4.ai bridges this gap with a tiny iOS app that syncs HealthKit data to a cloud database, then exposes
      it to your AI through a standard MCP server. Setup takes under 5 minutes.
    </p>

    <!-- Setup guide -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-base mb-6">Setting up — step by step</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="flex gap-5">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/15 border border-green-500/30 flex items-center justify-center text-green-400 font-bold text-sm">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Download the health4.ai app</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Install health4.ai from the App Store. On first launch, tap <strong class="text-neutral-300">Get Started</strong> and proceed through the Welcome and Privacy screens.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="flex gap-5">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/15 border border-green-500/30 flex items-center justify-center text-green-400 font-bold text-sm">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Choose <em>health4.ai cloud</em></h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
              On the <strong class="text-neutral-300">Connect to your AI</strong> screen, tap <strong class="text-neutral-300">health4.ai cloud</strong>. The app generates a short setup code — it looks like this:
            </p>
            <pre class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg px-6 py-4 text-green-400 font-mono text-xl font-bold text-center tracking-widest">H4-SAGE-3817</pre>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs mt-2">The code expires in 30 minutes. Tap "Generate a new code" if it expires before you finish.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="flex gap-5">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/15 border border-green-500/30 flex items-center justify-center text-green-400 font-bold text-sm">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Tell your AI to set you up</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
              The app shows a pre-written prompt — tap the copy button next to it, then open your AI (Claude, Cursor, Continue, etc.) and paste it. It reads:
            </p>
            <blockquote class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-neutral-300 text-sm italic leading-relaxed">
              "I just downloaded health4.ai. Please set up my health data table. My setup code is: <span class="text-green-400 not-italic font-mono">H4-SAGE-3817</span>"
            </blockquote>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">
              Your AI calls the <code class="text-green-300 bg-neutral-900 px-1 rounded text-xs">health4_register</code> tool, creates your personal data table, and responds with a <strong class="text-neutral-300">sync token</strong> and instructions for adding health4.ai to your AI's MCP configuration.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 p-4 bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs mb-2 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide">What your AI says back:</p>
              <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                "Your health data table is ready. Paste this sync token into the health4.ai app: <span class="text-green-400 font-mono text-xs">h4_sk_a3f9b2c1d4e5...</span>"
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-3 p-3 bg-amber-950/30 border border-amber-800/40 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-amber-400 text-xs font-medium mb-1">Need to add the health4.ai MCP to your AI first?</p>
              <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs leading-relaxed">
                For Claude Desktop: open <code class="text-neutral-300">claude_desktop_config.json</code>, add the server entry your AI provides, and restart Claude.
                The exact config block is included in your AI's setup response.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 4 -->
        <div class="flex gap-5">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/15 border border-green-500/30 flex items-center justify-center text-green-400 font-bold text-sm">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Paste your sync token into the app</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Tap <strong class="text-neutral-300">I've done it — paste my sync token</strong>, paste the <code class="text-green-300 bg-neutral-900 px-1 rounded text-xs">h4_sk_...</code> token your AI gave you, and tap <strong class="text-neutral-300">Verify & Connect</strong>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              The app validates the token with health4.ai and stores it securely in the iOS Keychain. The sync token is the app's permanent credential — it doesn't expire.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 5 -->
        <div class="flex gap-5">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/15 border border-green-500/30 flex items-center justify-center text-green-400 font-bold text-sm">5</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Grant HealthKit access — sync begins</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Tap <strong class="text-neutral-300">Allow Health Access</strong>. iOS shows the standard HealthKit permission sheet — you choose which data types to share. The app immediately starts syncing the past 30 days in the background.
            </p>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              From this point on, syncing is automatic. The app uses <code class="text-green-300 bg-neutral-900 px-1 rounded text-xs">HKObserverQuery</code> — iOS wakes it when new HealthKit data is written, even when the app is closed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 6 -->
        <div class="flex gap-5">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-pink-500/15 border border-pink-500/30 flex items-center justify-center text-pink-400 font-bold text-sm">✓</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Ask your AI about your health</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Once the first sync completes (usually 2–5 minutes), go back to your AI and ask:
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-2">
              {[
                "How was my sleep this week?",
                "Show me my HRV trend over the last 30 days",
                "How many workouts did I do last month?",
                "Compare my steps before and after my vacation"
              ].map(q => (
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-neutral-300">
                  <span class="text-pink-400 mt-0.5">›</span>
                  <span class="italic">"{q}"</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Edge cases / FAQ -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-base mb-5">Common questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5">

        <details class="group border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-300 cursor-pointer hover:text-white list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            My setup code expired before I finished
            <span class="text-neutral-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▾</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-neutral-800 pt-4">
            Tap <strong class="text-neutral-300">Generate a new code</strong> on the same screen. The old code is invalidated automatically. Go back to your AI with the new code and the whole exchange takes about 30 seconds.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-300 cursor-pointer hover:text-white list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            The token I pasted didn't work
            <span class="text-neutral-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▾</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-neutral-800 pt-4">
            Make sure you copied the full <code class="text-green-300 bg-neutral-900 px-1 rounded text-xs">h4_sk_…</code> token including the prefix. If the token starts with something else, your AI may not have the health4.ai MCP installed — check its setup response for the MCP configuration block.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-300 cursor-pointer hover:text-white list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            My AI doesn't know what health4.ai is
            <span class="text-neutral-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-colors">▾</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-neutral-800 pt-4">
            The health4.ai MCP needs to be added to your AI's config first. In Claude Desktop, open
            <code class="text-green-300 bg-neutral-900 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code>
            and add the <code class="text-green-300 bg-neutral-900 px-1 rounded text-xs">health4ai</code> server entry. See the GitHub README for the exact config.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-300 cursor-pointer hover:text-white list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Can I use health4.ai with multiple AIs?
            <span class="text-neutral-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▾</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-neutral-800 pt-4">
            Yes. Your MCP API key (the <code class="text-green-300 bg-neutral-900 px-1 rounded text-xs">h4_mk_…</code> key) works with any MCP-compatible AI: Claude, Cursor, Continue, Ollama with MCP support. Add the same MCP server entry — same URL, same key — to each AI's config.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-300 cursor-pointer hover:text-white list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            How do I revoke access?
            <span class="text-neutral-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▾</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-neutral-800 pt-4">
            In the app: go to <strong class="text-neutral-300">Connection</strong> tab → <strong class="text-neutral-300">Revoke access</strong>. This immediately invalidates both your sync token and MCP API key. Your historical data remains in the database; to delete it, tap <strong class="text-neutral-300">Delete my data</strong> in the same screen.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-300 cursor-pointer hover:text-white list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            I prefer to host my own database
            <span class="text-neutral-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▾</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-neutral-800 pt-4">
            On the <strong class="text-neutral-300">Connect to your AI</strong> screen, choose <strong class="text-neutral-300">Self-hosted</strong> instead. Enter your own Supabase project URL + anon key, or any REST endpoint that accepts JSON POST requests. The schema is documented on <a href="https://github.com/jefflitt1/health4ai" class="text-green-400 hover:underline">GitHub</a>.
          </p>
        </details>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Architecture (condensed) -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-base mb-4">Under the hood</h2>
      <pre class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-5 text-xs text-green-300 leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto">iPhone (health4.ai iOS app)
  └─ HKObserverQuery ──► new HealthKit sample arrives
  └─ BGProcessingTask ──► runs while charging
         │  POST /healthkit-ingest   Bearer h4_sk_...
         ▼
  health4.ai Supabase DB
  ├── healthkit_metrics       (raw samples, 30-day rolling window)
  └── healthkit_daily_summaries  (pre-aggregated, multi-year)
         │  mcp_api_key = h4_mk_...
         ▼
  mcp.health4.ai  (FastMCP, HTTP transport)
  11 tools: get_sleep · get_hrv_trend · get_workouts ·
            get_daily_snapshot · query_metric · get_health_summary ·
            get_long_term_trend · search_records · get_metric_stats ·
            compare_periods · get_coaching_brief
         │
         ▼
  Claude / Cursor / Continue / Ollama</pre>
      <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs mt-3">
        The sync token (app credential) and MCP API key (AI credential) are different. The app can never read your data; your AI can never write to it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="border-t border-neutral-800/60 pt-10">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/jefflitt1/health4ai"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-700 text-white text-sm px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg hover:border-green-500/50 hover:text-green-300 transition-colors"
        >
          GitHub →
        </a>
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-500 text-white text-sm px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg transition-colors"
        >
          Join the waitlist
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer class="border-t border-neutral-800/60 px-6 py-8 mt-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4 text-neutral-600 text-xs">
      <span>© 2026 health4.ai · Not a medical device</span>
      <div class="flex gap-6">
        <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-neutral-400 transition-colors">Privacy</a>
        <a href="/terms" class="hover:text-neutral-400 transition-colors">Terms</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/jefflitt1/health4ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:text-neutral-400 transition-colors">GitHub →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
